ng/Wireimage）" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Chappell-Roan-performing-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Chappell-Roan-performing-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Chappell-Roan-performing-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Chappell-Roan-performing-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Chappell-Roan-performing-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Chappell-Roan-performing-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3822738" class="wp-caption-text">查佩尔·罗恩（Chappell Roan）于2024年8月1日在伊利诺伊州芝加哥的2024年格兰特公园（Grant Park）演出。 （图片由Erika Goldring/Wireimage/Getty Images）</figcaption></figure><p>阿丽亚娜·格兰德（Ariana Grande）的评论是在查佩尔·罗恩（Chappell Roan）因呼吁娱乐业而成为格莱美奖的头条新闻之后的一周，并<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grammys-2025-chappell-roans-best-new-artist-acceptance-speech-demands-record-labels-treat-their-artists-as-valuable-employees-3833896">“要求该行业的标签从艺术家中获利数百万美元的艺术家将提供可宜居的工资和卫生保健，尤其是发展中的艺术家。”</a></p><p>查佩尔·罗恩（Chappell Roan）因长期音乐主管，前纽约大学克莱夫·戴维斯学院（Clive Davis Institute）的前主席杰弗里·拉布（Jeffrey Rabhan）的演讲而受到批评，后者在<a href="https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/music-news/chappell-roan-grammys-speech-misguided-1236128051/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>好莱坞记者</em></a>中回应了她的话，称她的格莱美族讲话“误导”和“未知”。</p><p>此后，罗恩（Roan）与<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/noah-kahan">诺亚·卡汉（Noah Kahan）</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/charli-xcx">查理（Charli XCX）</a>一样， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/chappell-roan-responds-to-op-ed-criticising-grammys-speech-they-best-put-their-money-where-their-mouth-is-otherwise-move-out-of-the-way-3836413">向支持艺术家的组织捐赠了25,000美元</a>。 </p><figure id="attachment_3814097" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3814097" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" clas